		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I envisioned the following work flow:
<br /><ol style="list-style-type: decimal"><li>Import .nes ROM in NESst </li><li>Export tilesets A and B </li><li>Scribble on them in a paint program </li><li>Import tilesets into NESst </li><li>Save CHR data back to .nes ROM </li></ol>
<br />When I export tileset as image from NESst under Wine 1.3.28, it comes out as a 24-bit BMP. But when I reimport the 24-bit bitmap into NESst, NESst tells me it can import only 4- or 8-bit BMP. Why doesn't NESst save a 4-bit BMP in the first place? Or does it save a 4-bit BMP under genuine Windows?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


